;LOOP 23 - 27, WHICH IS NEAR THE ACTIVE SITE AND
PARTICIPATES IN THE SUBUNIT INTERFACE, IS MOBILE, HAS
ONLY POOR DENSITY AND THE COORDINATES ARE NOT RELIABLE.
IN COMPARISON WITH THE ZINC-CONTAINING STRUCTURE,
ADDITIONAL DENSITY APPEARED FOR RESIDUES 207 - 210; STILL,
THE FIVE C-TERMINAL RESIDUES 211 - 215 CANNOT BE LOCATED
IN THE ELECTRON DENSITY MAP.

THE OCCUPANCY OF SULFATE ION 301 WAS REFINED TO 0.74.
